On 28 Oct 1994, Doug McIntyre wrote:

> As a Help Desk consultant, I've recieved the following message
> 
> > My other message is in reference to the fact that after sending a message 
> > to someone that I want to save my copy in a specific folder, right now, I 
> > have to go into the sent mail folder, select the message and then save 
> > it to the desired folder.  This is, in my opinion an unnecessary hastle.  
> 
> Does any one have a "slicker" way to save sent mail into differing folders?

Three:

a) Set up an alias. A little known feature of 3.90/3.91 is that there is 
a 4th field in each alias which is precisely the default Fcc: for that 
alias, so each persons mail will go to the right place.

b) Using Setup Config set the default-composer-headers to include fcc, 
then the standard fcc is displayed when composing and can be overwritten 
to whatever is required (^K then new value)

c) without either of those: when composing and in the headers type ^R 
(Rich Headers) upon which the fcc will be displayed; over write it with 
desired value.
