On Wed, 9 Nov 1994, Brad wrote:

> Firstly, a question: 
> 
> 	What does sorting by OrderedSubj do? I can't work that one out. 

First it sorts by subject, then it sorts the groups of messages with the 
same subject by the date of the oldest message in the group.  So it is 
the same as sort by subject except that the new "threads" are later in 
the index than the old "threads".
 
> Secondly, a recommendation (well, just sommat I've noticed, really): 
> 
> 	How about if .pinerc actually reflected compile-time options you
> set. e.g., from my .pinerc: 

This makes sense but probably isn't worth changing at this point.  It 
used to be that people looked at their pinerc files and edited them but 
now most people change configs with the Setup/Config screen.

> 	--Simon. 

