rv@cslab9a.cs.brown.edu (rodrigo vanegas) writes:
>How can i burst mailing list digests with Pine?

One way is to pipe the message through ``formail -ds'' and put the output 
into a folder.  E.g., while viewing the message do the following:

Type...                           In order to...
-------                           --------------
|                                 Pipe
formail -ds >> ~/mail/burst       Split the digest into individual
                                  messages and put them in a folder named
                                  ~/mail/burst.  (Replace ~/mail
                                  with your folder directory.)
g                                 Go to folder named...
burst                             burst


Note that in order for this to work you need to set enable-unix-pipe-cmd.

Hope this helps,
Nancy



