We need some help with PC-Pine 3.89, which we have installed on our PCs
(with FTP INC. PC-TCP).
We are already using Pine 3.89 on Unix and have an impad server on one of
the Suns, which we manage to access from the other workstations.
Our problems is the setting of the varialbe TZ (Time Zone).
In our first installation (some months ago) we set TZ=MET+DST but with 
this value Pine was not able to read mails because insted of write "MET" 
in mail headers it wrote "+DS". 
So we tried the new setting: TZ=   MET+DST (with tree blanks) and we 
have had not more problems. Unfortunately, some days ago, some our 
users were not again able to read their mails because in their mail headers 
