Here's a bit of .procmailrc that works for me:

     PATH=/bin:/usr/bin:/usr/local/bin
     MAILDIR=$HOME/mail      #you'd better make sure it exists
     DEFAULT=$MAILDIR/mbox
     LOGFILE=$MAILDIR/from
     :0:
     * ^Cc:.*imap
     Saved-Imap-Messages
     :0:
     * ^To:.*imap
     Saved-Imap-Messages

Any mail with "imap" in the To: or Cc: lines gets filed in the folder 
Saved-Imap-Messages and it shows up in the folder listing when I type 
"L".  This should work with 3.89 and 3.91 just fine!

