Kirk,
  The short answer is "no".  PCPine needs an IMAP server and can't use a 
POP or SMTP server for reading mail, though it does use SMTP for sending 
mail.  Also, the important thing is the protocol, not the port number.  
It's possible to set up a POP server on port 143 but it cause all sorts 
of havoc because programs connecting to port 143 would expect the IMAP 
protocol, not the POP protocol.

