Agreed.  The pine folks sometimes seem to be not listening, but I
believe they are listening very intently.  Pine's elegance as a mail
user agent could not have happened in a vacuum.

The problem with gatewaying News to email usually arises because the
email and News models are so dissimilar.  Email software is generally
designed -- with good reason -- to ensure that the user sees every
message, and no message is deleted without careful consideration.  News
software is generally designed -- with good reason -- to ensure that
the user sees no more than he explicitly wishes to, and that he finds
it easy to skip entire discussion threads, all postings from selected
people, etc.

The gatewaying leads to a serious conflict between the models.  Usually
it's the people who read via email who find it hard to cope.  They are
seeing too much.  Their email software is doing its job -- but it's the
wrong job.
