If you have root access, get Richard Gooch's PGPsendmail at
ftp.atnf.csiro.au:/pub/people/rgooch.  It's a drop in wrapper for sendmail
that makes PGP encryption completely transparent.  Some other tools come
with it that make decryption as transparent as it's likely to get.  You
wouldn't need root access if pine would allow the user to point pine to
something other than sendmail. 

