I had problems myself with this feature.  Here is what I found.

Pine appends the value of the <Path:> statement in .mh_profile to your 
$HOME directory name.  This will be the path where Pine will look for mh 
folders.  For example, if your <Path:> in .mh_profile is:
Path: mh-folders
and you <Go> #MH/project, Pine will look for the directory 
$HOME/mh-folders/project
By the same token, #MH/[] will refer to the collection of folders found 
in $HOME/mh-folders.

This might fit your case.
